{"serial": "00100", "department_serial": 4, "code": "LN2012", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Business English", "ch": "商用英文"}, "notice": {"en": "Undergraduate course. Course level: Upper-intermediate.Unexcused first class absence will result in a reduction in grade. The lecturer can withdraw the absentees from the first 2 classes.", "ch": "中高級課程。大學部課程。 建議TOEIC多益英語測驗程度600分以上的學生選修。分發條件:(1)上課缺席者，須和學校請假，否則扣學期總成績。(2)前兩週未出席者，老師有權退選該生。(3)修過職場英文者，禁修商用英文."}, "instructor": {"en": ["Wang, Li-Jen"], "ch": ["王立仁"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "TR", "room": "A202"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "語言中心", "en": "Language Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 1, "selected": 42, "remark": {"ch": "中高級課程。大學部課程。 建議TOEIC多益英語測驗程度600分以上的學生選修。分發條件:(1)上課缺席者，須和學校請假，否則扣學期總成績。(2)前兩週未出席者，老師有權退選該生。(3)修過職場英文者，禁修商用英文.", "en": "Undergraduate course. Course level: Upper-intermediate.Unexcused first class absence will result in a reduction in grade. The lecturer can withdraw the absentees from the first 2 classes."}, "goal": {"ch": "課程目標如下：\n1.建立學生基礎商業英文的概念\n2.熟悉英文電子郵件的寫作模式\n3.理解商業英文的各種情境\n4.懂得如何在各種商務情境進行適當的英文對話\n5.提升英文簡報的能力\n6.培養使用英文進行會議的技巧", "en": "The course objectives are as follows:\n1.Establish a foundation of concepts in business English for students.\n2.Familiarize students with the writing patterns of English emails.\n3.Understand various contexts of business English.\n4.Acquire the ability to engage in appropriate English conversations in various business situations.\n5.Enhance skills in delivering English presentations.\n6.Cultivate techniques for conducting meetings in English."}, "outline": {"ch": "課程介紹和預測測驗\n單元1: 建立聯繫（寫作：個人簡介）\n單元1: 建立聯繫\n單元2: 國際設計（口語：團隊會議）\n單元3: 未來生活方式（寫作：電子郵件寫作1）\n單元3: 未來生活方式（寫作：電子郵件寫作1）\n單元4: 文化遺產（口語：演講技巧1）\n單元5: 時尚與功能（口語：電話交談、給予建議和提供意見）\n期中考\n單元6: 利用創新（口語：演講技巧2）\n單元7: 工作風格與職業（寫作：電子郵件寫作2）\n單元7: 工作風格與職業（寫作：電子郵件寫作2）\n單元8: 流程（口語：時間管理）\n單元9: 運動商務（口語：面試）\n期末專案演示（小組）\n期末考\n彈性學習週（將分發作業）\n彈性學習週（將分發作業）", "en": "1Course Introduction and pretest\n2Unit 1: Making connections (Writing: Profile)\n3Unit 1: Making connections\n4Unit 2: International design (Speaking: Team meeting)\n5Unit 3: Future lifestyles (Writing: Email writing 1)\n6Unit 3: Future lifestyles (Writing: Email writing\n1)\n7Unit 4: Heritage (Speaking: Presentation skills 1)\n8Unit 5: Fashion and function (Speaking: Telephoning, giving advice and suggestions)\n9Midterm\n10Unit 6: Using innovation (Speaking: Presentation skills 2)\n11Unit 7: Work styles and careers (Writing: Email writing 2)\n12Unit 7: Work styles and careers (Writing: Email writing 2)\n13Unit 8: Processes (Speaking: Time management)\n14Unit 9: The business of sport (Speaking: Job interview)\n15Final Project Presentation (Group)\n16Final exam\n17Self-learning week (Assignments will be given)\n18Self-learning week (Assignments will be given)"}, "textbook": {"ch": "1.Go Global-English for Global Business, Garry Pearson, Graham Skerritt, Hiroshi YOSHIZUKA, Cosmos Culture Ltd, 2020 (ISBN978-986-318-915-2)\n2.International Express – Intermediate, Keith Harding ＆amp; Alistair Lane, Oxford University Press, 2014 (ISBN978-0-19-459786-9)", "en": "1.Go Global-English for Global Business, Garry Pearson, Graham Skerritt, Hiroshi YOSHIZUKA, Cosmos Culture Ltd, 2020 (ISBN978-986-318-915-2)\n2.International Express – Intermediate, Keith Harding ＆amp; Alistair Lane, Oxford University Press, 2014 (ISBN978-0-19-459786-9)"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "10", "en": "10"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n\n\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "", "", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "出席率（10％）：\n參與度（10％）：\n期中考試（20％）和期末考試（20％）：\n作業（15％）：\n小考（10％）：\n期末小組報告（15％）：", "en": "1.Attendance (10％):\nAttendance is mandatory. For each class-hour absence, 2 points will be deducted from the final grade. A medical leave requires proof of medical care, and all other excused leaves also require proof. All students are expected to attend class on time; for each tardiness, 1 point will be deducted. An absence of more than 5 class-hours will result in a failing grade for the course. Please note that students who miss the first class will not be allowed to take this course.\n2.Participation (10％):\nStudents enrolled in this course must actively participate in in-class events.\n3.Midterm Exam (20％) and Final Exam (20％):\nBoth exams include sections on speaking, writing, reading, and listening. All question types will be introduced at least two weeks in advance.\n4.Weekly Assignments (15％):\nStudents will receive course-related writing assignments.\n5.Quizzes (10％):\n6.Group Presentation (15％):\n7.Around week 15, all students will deliver oral presentations based on the materials learned in groups."}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期三 2,3,4節", "en": "Wednesday 9:00-11:50"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "學生於彈性教學週將探索與商業英文情境相關的素材，並作課程反思。", "en": "During the flexible teaching week, students will explore materials related to business English situations and conduct course reflections."}, "domain": {"ch": "應用英文", "en": "應用英文"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "語言溝通", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "文化視野", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習"]}, {"competencies": "自主學習", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "作品/創作展演"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Language & Communication Skills", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance", "Products/Creative Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Intercultural Literacy", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments"]}, {"competencies": "Self-directed Lifelong Learning", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Products/Creative Performance"]}]}, "assig